thread.title: S.J. boys: Cherokee moves on in Coaches Tournament
thread.title_full: S.J. boys: Cherokee moves on in Coaches Tournament

title: S.J. boys: Cherokee moves on in Coaches Tournament
text:
Washington Township 4, Burlington Township 0: John Dalessandro scored a goal and had two assists for the home team.
BURLINGTON COUNTY LEAGUE 
Pemberton 4, Burlington City 2: Cedric Konan's hat trick and assist led the way for the hosts. Nazir Britt also scored. 
Westampton Tech 6, Camden County Tech 0: Christopher Hernandez and Isaias Rodriguez each scored twice on the road. Dogukan Ozdemir and Eren Ozturk also scored a goal each. 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE 
Lenape 2, Seneca 1: Alec Cruz and Peter Monti both scored in the second half for the visitors. Jack Guerrieri made six saves in net. 
TRI-COUNTY DIAMOND 
Schalick 4, Delsea 1: Collin Cardona tallied a goal and an assist at home. Michael D'Orio, Dan Farrell, and Tyler Lunsford also added a goal each. 
Woodstown 4, Deptford 1: Trey Parker's two goals led the way for the visitors, and Geoff Schaefer and Dylan Varner also scored. 
TRI-COUNTY CLASSIC 
Gloucester Catholic 6, Gloucester 0: Chris Kain scored a hat trick to pace the visitors' offense. Ray Anzola, Joe Grace, and Justin Phy each scored. 
TRI-COUNTY ROYAL 
Clearview 5, GCIT 0: Nick Scanzano's two goals and one assist led the way for the hosts. Gavin Hunter, Blake Logan, and Andrew Norcross also scored. 
CAPE-ATLANTIC LEAGUE 
Cedar Creek 3, Buena 0: Brinton Shinn scored two goals, and Jose Contreras scored once for the home team. 
Ocean City 6, Vineland 0: Aaron King's hat trick, along with two goals from Matt Brook led the charge for the hosts. Jimmy Flukey also scored. 
Pleasantville 5, Wildwood Catholic 2: Oscar Mancia tallied two goals and an assist at home. CROSS-COUNTRY 
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE CHAMPIONSHIPS 
Cherry Hill East's Aaron Groff finished the course at Rowan in 15 minutes and 13 seconds to win the individual title. Cherokee edged Cherry Hill East, 43-44, to win the team championship.
